rootProject.name = "QwenVision" include(":app"){ "models": [ { "name": "Qwen2.5-VL-3B-Instruct q4", "modelId": "litert-community/Qwen2.5-VL-3B-Instruct", "modelFile": "Qwen2.5-VL-3B-Instruct_q4.task", "description": "Qwen2.5-VL 3B multimodal vision-language model with 4-bit quantization. Supports image understanding, OCR, object detection descriptions, and contextual image Q&A. Runs fully on-device via MediaPipe LLM Inference API.", "sizeInBytes": 2100000000, "version": "20250520", "llmSupportImage": true, "defaultConfig": { "topK": 40, "topP": 0.95, "temperature": 0.7, "maxTokens": 2048, "accelerators": "gpu,cpu" }, "taskTypes": ["llm_ask_image", "llm_chat"] }, { "name": "Qwen2.5-VL-7B-Instruct q4", "modelId": "litert-community/Qwen2.5-VL-7B-Instruct", "modelFile": "Qwen2.5-VL-7B-Instruct_q4.task", "description": "Qwen2.5-VL 7B — the flagship multimodal vision-language model with 4-bit quantization. Excels at scene understanding, document parsing, chart reading, and multi-turn image conversations. Runs fully on-device via MediaPipe LLM Inference API.", "sizeInBytes": 4800000000, "version": "20250520", "llmSupportImage": true, "defaultConfig": { "topK": 40, "topP": 0.95, "temperature": 0.7, "maxTokens": 2048, "accelerators": "gpu,cpu" }, "taskTypes": ["llm_ask_image", "llm_chat"] }, { "name": "Qwen2.5-1.5B-Instruct q8", "modelId": "litert-community/Qwen2.5-1.5B-Instruct", "modelFile": "Qwen2.5-1.5B-Instruct_multi-prefill-seq_q8_ekv1280.task", "description": "Qwen2.5 1.5B text-only LLM with 8-bit quantization. Ideal for fast on-device text tasks, summarization, and follow-up questions after image analysis.", "sizeInBytes": 1625493432, "version": "20250514", "llmSupportImage": false, "defaultConfig": { "topK": 40, "topP": 0.95, "temperature": 1.0, "maxTokens": 1024, "accelerators": "cpu" }, "taskTypes": ["llm_chat"] } ] }# Qwen Vision — On-Device AI Image Analysis
An Android app for **fully on-device image analysis and context extraction** powered by the **Qwen2.5-VL** multimodal vision-language model series, built using the architecture patterns from Google AI Edge Gallery.
---
## Features
| Feature | Detail | |---|---| | 🖼️ **Image Analysis** | Upload any photo — scenes, documents, charts, handwriting | | 🔍 **Context Extraction** | Objects, text (OCR), layout, relationships, metadata | | 💬 **Multi-turn Chat** | Ask follow-up questions about the same image | | ⚡ **Quick Presets** | One-tap prompts: Describe, Extract Text, Objects, Analyze Chart | | 📵 **Fully On-Device** | Zero network calls during inference — works offline | | 🔒 **Private** | Images never leave your phone | | 🎛️ **Configurable** | Tune top-K, top-P, temperature, GPU/CPU backend per model |
---
## Supported Models
All models download from HuggingFace and run via **MediaPipe LLM Inference API** (LiteRT `.task` format).
| Model | Size | Vision | Best For | |---|---|---|---| | `Qwen2.5-VL-3B-Instruct q4` | ~2.1 GB | ✅ | Fast image Q&A, OCR, object ID | | `Qwen2.5-VL-7B-Instruct q4` | ~4.8 GB | ✅ | Detailed scene understanding, charts, documents | | `Qwen2.5-1.5B-Instruct q8` | ~1.6 GB | ❌ | Text chat, follow-up reasoning |
> ⚠️ **Note**: LiteRT-quantized `.task` files for Qwen2.5-VL must be available on HuggingFace `litert-community` org. Check availability or convert using LiteRT tools if not yet published.
---
## Architecture
Follows the [Google AI Edge Gallery](https://github.com/google-ai-edge/ai-edge-gallery) architecture:
``` app/ ├── data/ │ ├── Model.kt # Model data class with config accessors │ ├── Config.kt # Typed config system (slider, toggle, dropdown) │ ├── ConfigValue.kt # Sealed ConfigValue (Int/Float/String) │ ├── Tasks.kt # Task definitions (LLM_ASK_IMAGE, LLM_CHAT) │ ├── ModelAllowlist.kt # JSON deserialization + task population │ └── DownloadRepository.kt # HuggingFace download with progress │ ├── ui/ │ ├── theme/ # Qwen dark theme (ink + cyan palette) │ ├── home/ # HomeScreen with task cards + model status │ ├── qwenvision/ │ │ ├── QwenModelHelper.kt # MediaPipe LlmInference + session mgmt │ │ ├── QwenVisionViewModel.kt # Streaming inference ViewModel │ │ └── QwenVisionScreen.kt # Full UI: image picker, presets, chat │ ├── modelmanager/ │ │ └── ModelManagerViewModel.kt # Download + init state management │ └── navigation/ │ └── QwenNavGraph.kt # Compose Navigation │ ├── QwenApplication.kt # Loads model_allowlist.json at startup └── MainActivity.kt ```
### Key Patterns (from Google AI Edge Gallery)
1. **Task → Models → Allowlist**: Tasks hold a `MutableList<Model>`, populated at runtime from `model_allowlist.json` via `populateTasksFromAllowlist()`.
2. **Model Instance lifecycle**: `model.instance` holds a `QwenModelInstance(engine, session)`. The ViewModel waits for `instance != null` before inference.
3. **Streaming via `resultListener`**: MediaPipe fires `(partialResult: String, done: Boolean)` callbacks. The ViewModel removes the loading bubble on first token and appends partial tokens using `updateLastTextMessageContentIncrementally()`.
4. **llmSupportImage flag**: Controls `setMaxNumImages(1)` and `setEnableVisionModality(true)` in MediaPipe options. Only vision models show the image picker.
5. **ConfigKey system**: Per-model config values stored in `model.configValues: Map<ConfigKey, ConfigValue>`, with typed accessors `getIntConfigValue`, `getFloatConfigValue`.
---
## Setup
### 1. Prerequisites - Android Studio Hedgehog or newer - Android device or emulator with API 26+ (Android 8.0) - ~5–10 GB free storage for models
### 2. Clone and open ```bash git clone <this-repo> # Open Android/src/ in Android Studio ```
### 3. Build ```bash cd Android/src ./gradlew assembleDebug ```
### 4. Download models On first launch, tap a task card → model card shows "Download" button. Models download from HuggingFace (~2–5 GB each). Wi-Fi recommended.
### 5. Load model After download, tap "Load Model" to initialize MediaPipe inference engine (~30–60s on first load).
---
## Adding New Qwen Models
Edit `model_allowlist.json` in `assets/`:
```json { "name": "Qwen2.5-VL-2B-Instruct q4", "modelId": "litert-community/Qwen2.5-VL-2B-Instruct", "modelFile": "Qwen2.5-VL-2B-Instruct_q4.task", "description": "...", "sizeInBytes": 1500000000, "version": "20250601", "llmSupportImage": true, "defaultConfig": { "topK": 40, "topP": 0.95, "temperature": 0.7, "maxTokens": 2048 }, "taskTypes": ["llm_ask_image", "llm_chat"] } ```
---
## Hardware Requirements
| Tier | Min RAM | Recommended | |---|---|---| | 3B VL model (q4) | 4 GB | 6 GB+ | | 7B VL model (q4) | 8 GB | 12 GB+ |
GPU acceleration (Vulkan/OpenCL) significantly improves token speed. Falls back to CPU automatically.
---
## Privacy
- All model inference runs on-device - No telemetry, no analytics, no network calls during chat - Downloaded model files stored in app's external files directory - Images are processed in-memory only — never written to disk
---
